quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,67,"And when harm touches you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>at sea,<i class=""s"">(all) </i>those you call upon become lost except for Him. But when He delivered{1}you to the shore, you disregarded<i class=""s"">(Him) </i>; thus man has always been a staunch denier.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from present tense to past tense.
  17,68,"Are you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>confident that <span class=""h"">He<sup foot_note=""80447"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will not cause a side of the shore to collapse</span>beneath you or unleash a tornado against you, and then you find no trustee?"
  17,69,"Or are you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>confident that <span class=""h"">He<sup foot_note=""80448"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will not return you</span>to it once again and unleash a hurricane of <span class=""h"">wind<sup foot_note=""80449"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span>against you <span class=""h"">and</span><span class=""h"">drown<sup foot_note=""80450"" class=""qiraat"">3</sup> </span>you for your denial, and then you find no attending followers against Us?"
  17,70,"Yet very truly We have honored the Children of Adam and carried them on land and sea and provided them with good things and greatly favored them over many of those We have created."
  17,71,"On the day when We call every group of people by their leader, then whoever is given his record{1}in his right hand—those will read their record, and they will not be dealt with unjustly by as much as the hair upon a date-stone.",footnotes:1:Literally ‘scripture’.
  17,72,"But whoever is blind in this<i class=""s"">(life) </i>—he will be blind in the Hereafter and further astray from the way."
  17,73,"And they almost lured you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>away from what We have revealed to you so that you would fabricate something else in Our name, and in that case they would have taken you for a close friend."
  17,74,"Had We not given you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>stability, you were about to incline towards them a little."
  17,75,"Then We would have made you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>taste double in life and double at death, then you would have found for yourself no supporter against Us."
